	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ice Silk Armor is made using the swatches of Ice Silk dropped from Ice Burrowers.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ice Burrowers are level 60-61 leeches that inhabit the Western Wastes, home of numerous level 60+ dragons.  Each swatch requires to silks combined in a Coldain Tanner's Kit.  The Kit is also required to make the armor, and can be bought in Thurgadin.<br><br>Platinum Silk [Velious]<br>Vial of Purified Mana<br>Pattern<br>Ice Silk Swatch (1) [Velious]<br><br>The purified mana is made by enchanters using a poison vial, and 4 rubies as regeants, and it is a 49th level spell.  The worms also drop some nice monk chest armor with the fourth highest possible AC available for a monk in all of Norrath, surpassed only by Phase Spider, Icicle, and Flayed Paebala.  You could try a Tree Weave if you can manage to keep the rest of your equipment under 2lbs. without inventory.  It also has very nice Cold Resist.  Back on topic, it shouldn't be too difficult to form a WW army for dragons and leeches, with the sought after dragon loot and the Skin...  Anyway...  Good luck.  Although the amice may not be worth the near 1000 platinum it takes to make, I hear the other pieces may be.  Be safe.<br>&nbsp;<br>Hyden Endabrush<br>Expert Scout of the Fay</td></tr>
